718590f-a.title: Manhattan: Centre Street - Walker Street
718590f-a.text:
148 Centre Street, at the 5.E. corner of Walker Street (left),
showtng a large lot 91.7x129 in an undeveloped state. The present
appearance of same has continued for over 2O years. To the left
appears the side wall of the structure occupied by Moe Levy (Clothiers)
for years and a feature of this vicinity.
June 10, 1938.
N. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

718591f-a.title: Manhattan: Centre Street - Walker Street
718591f-a.text:
1)
Centre Street, south from Walker Street, and showing at Foley
Square several civic, state and federal structures, prominent of
which are, the New York State Bldg., the Federal Courts Bldg. and the
Nunicipal Bldg. Dimily seen on the right is the old Tombs nrison,
onposite a clearance where a new Criminal Courts (and prison) Bldg.
will rise.
June 10, 1938.
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
TRe Tombs and the Board of Health Bldg. on the west side of Centre
Street, occupying the blocks from Franklin to Worth Streets, as view-
eed southwestward from White Street and across the westerly side of
the new court site.
June 10, 1938.
P. L. Sperr
NO RPPRODUCTIONS.
